===Etymology===
A learned 17th-century coinage, from [[mono-]] ({{term|μονός||one|tr=monós|lang=grc}}) and -[[theism]] ({{term|θεός||god, [[deity]]|tr=theós|lang=grc}} + {{term|lang=grc|-ισμός|tr=-ismos}}) The term parallels the earlier [[polytheism]], [[atheism]] (the simplex [[theism]] being slightly later).
The earliest known use is by Henry More, ca. 1660, in explicit juxtaposition with both ''atheism'' and ''polytheism''.

